lead_paragraph: Giannis Antetokounmpo had 27 points, 12 rebounds and 10 assists, and the Milwaukee Bucks beat the Los Angeles Lakers 108-101 on Monday night in retiring star Kobe Bryant's last trip to the Bradley Center.

headline.print_headline: Bucks Beat Lakers 108-101 in Kobe's Final Game in Milwaukee
